Rating: 3
This was a very yummy recipe and I have no reservations about giving these out to my friends this Christmas. I did have to add an extra 1/4 milk because the dough was dry. I also took some other reviewers' advice and doubled the spices and omitted the raisins in favour of crystallized ginger. To make them more festive, I dipped the tops in milk and then dipped them in fine sugar before baking. It gave them a beautiful "snowy" topping. These are definitely worth keeping in the holiday baking rotation!

Rating: 4
I have made these scones for Christmas Day since the recipe was released. Although my family has always loved the, I found them a little dry. After reading the other reviews, I added some plain yogurt to the scones this year and it made all the difference. I also find that they don't need 25 minutes in the oven - 20 minutes is plenty.

