Yummy. I've made this twice so far. Once as written which was good. The second time I doubled the spices and raisins (using half golden) and they were delicious. I also dropped the batter in mounds on the baking sheet and prefered the results over the wedges (plus its easier).

Rating: 3
Tasty scones! I was out of ground ginger so I used some finely chopped candied ginger - it worked nicely. I also used 1/2 whole wheat flour, I enjoy the heartier taste of it and they weren't too heavy.

Rating: 4
If anyone wants to know what happens if you accidently add 3/4 cup milk instead of 1/4, read on... I was in a tizzy over what to do when I realized I didn't have a dough to roll out. I put my bad luck down to the high heat and humidity of the summer. (I realized my mistake about 1/2 hour later.) I just put it in a loaf pan and baked for 25 minutes on Gas Mark 5 (as prescribed) and then turned it down to about Gas Mark 3 1/2 and baked another 25 minutes. It turned out absolutely perfect! Really moist. Will serve it for the mothers at baby group tomorrow. I can't believe my luck. Does anyone know why it worked?

